The article is a transcript of Vice President Mike Pence's remarks during his visit to Indonesia. He expresses condolences for the recent terrorist attack in Paris and reassures the people of Indonesia of the United States' commitment to combat terrorism. Pence also acknowledges the significance of Kartini Day, which celebrates women's empowerment in Indonesia. He discusses the strong economic partnership between the United States and Indonesia, highlighting the signing of major agreements worth over $10 billion between American and Indonesian businesses. Pence emphasizes the need to improve trade relations between the two countries and calls for reducing barriers to trade and investment. He also mentions President Trump's plans for tax reform and deregulation to stimulate economic growth in the United States. Pence concludes by expressing his admiration for Indonesia's commitment to religious tolerance and its role as a leader in the world.